founded in rotterdam in  it has over  offices worldwide and its largest operations are in geneva houston london and singapore its primary business is the trading and distribution of energy products globally including over  million bpd of crude oil and products and  million tonnes of lpg annually revenues in  were  billion hardy said “we are delighted to be working with adnoc on this longterm supply agreement lpg is an important clean fuel and this will support our growing downstream lpg business” vitol’s energy assets globally include over  million cubic metres of storage across six continents  bpd of refining capacity and shellbranded downstream businesses in  african countries as well as australia vitol also has the only independent longstanding refinery in fujairah vitol’s customers include national oil companies multinationals leading industrial and chemical companies and the world’s largest airlines about adnoc adnoc is a major diversified group of energy and petrochemical companies that produces  million barrels of oil and  billion cubic feet of raw gas a day its integrated upstream midstream and downstream activities are carried out by  specialist subsidiary and joint venture companies to find out more visit wwwadnocae for further information mediaadnocae lpg previous article next article media enquiries  jul  vitol’s coastal caverns announces plans for beaumont lpg export facility read more  mar  first gas delivered to new world class lpg terminal in nigeria read more home  vitol who we are who we are our companies vitol aviation valt varo vivo energy viva energy australia vpi immingham vtti ventspils nafta group cockett marine oil ovh energy our business in numbers vitol foundation what we do what we do refining atpc refinery bayernoil refinery cressier refinery fujairah refinery geelong refinery trading crude oil middle distillates gasoline naphtha lpg fuel oil bitumen methanol ethanol lng natural gas power coal iron ore alumina regulatory  sds documents s